body:
I debugged this for a bit and found that `LocalDiffAwareness` does not add the contents of moved directories to the list of changed paths. The following test case, when added to `LocalDiffAwarenessTest`, fails:

```java
  @Test
  public void testMoveDirectory() throws Exception {
    captureFirstView(watchFsEnabledProvider);

    mkdir("equestria");
    touch("equestria/foo.txt");
    new ModifiedFileSetChecker().modify("equestria").modify("equestria/foo.txt").check();

    testCaseRoot.getRelative("equestria").renameTo(testCaseRoot.getRelative("equestria2"));
    new ModifiedFileSetChecker()
        .modify("equestria")
        .modify("equestria/foo.txt")
        .modify("equestria2")
        .modify("equestria2/foo.txt")
        .check();
  }
```
```
missing (1): equestria/foo.txt
---
expected   : [equestria2/foo.txt, equestria2, equestria/foo.txt, equestria]
but was    : [equestria2/foo.txt, equestria2, equestria]
```

The invalidation in `FileSystemValueCheckerInferringAncestors` only affects the directory, not the individual `FileStateValue` for `app/Main.java`, which retains its state as existing throughout `demo.sh`. As a result, `typeChanged` is always `false` here
https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/blob/27de623cfbc05c6bfcb1a00065d1a890c2c31529/src/main/java/com/google/devtools/build/lib/skyframe/FileSystemValueCheckerInferringAncestors.java#L316-L320
and the `app` directory itself is never visited since no child ever returns `true`.

Changing
https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/blob/27de623cfbc05c6bfcb1a00065d1a890c2c31529/src/main/java/com/google/devtools/build/lib/skyframe/FileSystemValueCheckerInferringAncestors.java#L320
to `return true` fixes the issue, but that's of course not the right way to make this work. Perhaps the parent should always be visited if no child has been seen?

CC @meisterT
